On Thu, Apr 5, 2012 at 11:52 AM, Markus Lanthaler
&lt;markus.lanthaler@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; On Wednesday, April 04, 2012 11:35 PM, Mike Kelly wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; On Wed, Apr 4, 2012 at 4:01 PM, Markus Lanthaler wrote:
&gt;&gt; &gt; I&#39;m not trying to argue against you, but to understand. I believe we
&gt;&gt; have
&gt;&gt; &gt; quite similar goals, but follow different approaches to achieve them.
&gt;&gt; &gt; It would definitely help me if you could be a bit more concrete. So,
&gt;&gt; what&#39;s
&gt;&gt; &gt; the additional stuff JSON-LD drags along?
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; I don&#39;t know why the spec(s) is/are so long or how something that
&gt;&gt; should be simple is made to appear so convoluted, but my assumption is
&gt;&gt; that this is due to &#39;additional stuff&#39;?
&gt;
&gt; Well that&#39;s an another point then which has nothing to do with JSON-LD
&gt; itself.
&gt;
&gt; There are basically two reasons for this. First of all, we wanted to make
&gt; the spec very clear and understandable, therefore we probably described more
&gt; than would be really necessary. The other thing is that it is still a work
&gt; in progress. We have been working on it for quite some time and it just grew
&gt; to that size. If you check you&#39;ll actually see that most of the text are in
&gt; fact examples. I&#39;m quite sure before we consider it as stable - which
&gt; hopefully happens soon - we will be able to shorten the spec quite a bit. Of
&gt; course is also has some features which other approaches don&#39;t have, e.g.,
&gt; string internationalization. But you don&#39;t need to use them if you don&#39;t
&gt; need them.
&gt;
&gt; And by the way.. I&#39;ve never heard someone arguing that, e.g., HTML is too
&gt; complex because the spec is too long.
&gt;

The difference being, HTML has a lot more to concern itself with than
(what should be) a few conventions on top of JSON.

The JSON-LD spec says &quot;RDF can be expressed using JSON-LD&quot;.. Is this a
requirement for JSON-LD? Or could you strip it down to bear minimum
and forfeit that capability?

